summary:
An experienced business professional with two business-related masters degrees. Having successfully run a manufacturing and export business mainly in Pottery and Bamboo flower sticks in my native Myanmar, I was gifted the opportunity in 2009 to come to the Netherlands to further my education, as well as that of my son. After gaining my Master of Marketing from Tilburg University, I have overcome the challenges of assimilating to a new country, to establish two growing start-up businesses, which are consulting and trading. 

Founded FMK Business Support Co., Ltd in 2016 in Myanmar, import flower bulbs from the Netherlands and sell to the local growers and then expanded into importing new flower varieties from the Netherlands, grow in own farm in Ywarngan (Southern Shan) and selling and distributing under the brand name of FMK Flora. The latest expansion is the food safety project in Kawmhuu (Just next to Yangon) under the brand name of Agrim Co., Ltd. Signed the distributorship agreement with Rijkzwaan in January 2021.

Flee back to NL in April because of Military Coup in Myanmar and looking for job especially in Agriculture related field.
